coverage/
# Canonical human-edited data: per-dish files, the ingredient catalog, the
# history seed, and the structural changelog. Their byte layout is owned by the
# engine's round-trip serializer (engine/src/data/serialize.ts) and asserted
# byte-identical in CI, so Prettier must not reflow these markdown tables.
data/
design_handoff/
# Design-handoff reference prototypes (runnable HTML/JSX + assets), delivered
# as-is and owned by the handoff, not the formatter. Same rationale as
# design_handoff/ above; reflowing the prototype adds churn with no benefit.
features/*/handoff/
package-lock.json
# Frozen history: retired plans, handoffs, and specs kept for the record, not
# current truth. Reflowing them adds churn with no benefit.
archive/
# Machine-generated Convex client. Regenerated by `convex codegen`, so any
# formatting would be overwritten on the next generation.
app/convex/_generated/
# Append-only ledgers: chronological records, never rewritten by any pass (see
# MAINTENANCE.md). Kept out of the formatter for the same reason data/changelog.md
# is, so an append never has to satisfy Prettier's table/whitespace opinions.
DECISIONS.md
RETRO.md
docs/CHANGELOG.md
